cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV 

This paper is about neural machine translation, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes modifications to the Transformer architecture, which is a deep learning model, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves optimizing the training time, which could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper uses BLEU scores to evaluate the performance of the model, which is a metric commonly used in machine translation and could also fall under cs.CV (Computer Vision).
